Introduction to Linux and shells

Linux is an operating system, like macOS or Windows. It is also the most popular Open Source and free, as in freedom, operating system. It powers the vast majority of the servers that compose the Internet. It's the base upon which everything is built upon. But not just that. Android is
based on (a modified version of) Linux. The Linux "core" (called kernel) was born in 1991 in
Finland, and it went a really long way from its humble beginnings. It went on to be the kernel of the GNU Operating System, creating the duo GNU/L
